Text.SourceString: A new farmer in town?//You moved here <Italic>after</> the oil spill? Huh.//<portrait=normal>I’m <NPCName>Zarah</>. //See you around.
Text.LocalizedString: A new farmer in town?//You moved here <Italic>after</> the oil spill? Huh.//<portrait=normal>I’m <NPCName>Zarah</>. //See you around.

Text.SourceString: I was sailing the other day, and oh my, you wouldn't believe how much trash I saw at sea!//<portrait=annoyed>Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: I was sailing the other day, and oh my, you wouldn't believe how much trash I saw at sea!//<portrait=annoyed>Hmm…

Text.SourceString: It’s upsetting to see nature being covered in trash like that.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s upsetting to see nature being covered in trash like that.

Text.SourceString: Going on an adventure, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Going on an adventure, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: How was your weekend?//Oh, splendid to hear! Mine was a good one, thank you for asking.
Text.LocalizedString: How was your weekend?//Oh, splendid to hear! Mine was a good one, thank you for asking.

Text.SourceString: This morning, I woke up with the motivation of a sleepy sloth.//It's one of those peculiar days, I suppose.
Text.LocalizedString: This morning, I woke up with the motivation of a sleepy sloth.//It's one of those peculiar days, I suppose.

Text.SourceString: I kind of like it here on Coral Island.//<portrait=happy>Who knows? Maybe someday I’ll buy a house and move to a place that doesn’t rock…//<portrait=thinking>Sounds dull, to be honest.
Text.LocalizedString: I kind of like it here on Coral Island.//<portrait=happy>Who knows? Maybe someday I’ll buy a house and move to a place that doesn’t rock…//<portrait=thinking>Sounds dull, to be honest.

Text.SourceString: Oh, you’re the chatty type.//<portrait=normal>Don’t be insulted if I don’t say hi to you first, okay?//Probably I either don’t see you, or I’m too distracted to notice anything.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, you’re the chatty type.//<portrait=normal>Don’t be insulted if I don’t say hi to you first, okay?//Probably I either don’t see you, or I’m too distracted to notice anything.

Text.SourceString: If you’re looking for tips, I know a thing or two about combat.//<portrait=normal>For instance, you don’t want to go into combat without armor…//Common sense, yeah?
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re looking for tips, I know a thing or two about combat.//<portrait=normal>For instance, you don’t want to go into combat without armor…//Common sense, yeah?

Text.SourceString: Camping in a cavern for more than two days is a nasty business. I don’t miss it.//<portrait=annoyed>How can a place be damp and hot at the same time?
Text.LocalizedString: Camping in a cavern for more than two days is a nasty business. I don’t miss it.//<portrait=annoyed>How can a place be damp and hot at the same time?

Text.SourceString: There are ancient scrolls scattered around the island… It’s true.//<portrait=normal>But there’s no way of knowing exactly where they are.//So we just have to explore lots of different places.
Text.LocalizedString: There are ancient scrolls scattered around the island… It’s true.//<portrait=normal>But there’s no way of knowing exactly where they are.//So we just have to explore lots of different places.

Text.SourceString: I found some scrolls when I was fishing the other day. Fishing!//<portrait=surprised02>Who would’ve thought?
Text.LocalizedString: I found some scrolls when I was fishing the other day. Fishing!//<portrait=surprised02>Who would’ve thought?

Text.SourceString: Life feels bland when I’m not after something…//<portrait=annoyed>It's a pity, really. I feel stuck, you know? Like I'm trapped in an endless cycle of one adventure after another.
Text.LocalizedString: Life feels bland when I’m not after something…//<portrait=annoyed>It's a pity, really. I feel stuck, you know? Like I'm trapped in an endless cycle of one adventure after another.

Text.SourceString: Now, is that a good thing or a bad thing? I’ll let you decide.
Text.LocalizedString: Now, is that a good thing or a bad thing? I’ll let you decide.

Text.SourceString: I've got this wild hunch that there's more to this island than meets the eye.
Text.LocalizedString: I've got this wild hunch that there's more to this island than meets the eye.

Text.SourceString: Do you think it's up to us to uncover its hidden wonders?//Or should we just wait patiently until nature decides to spill the beans?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think it's up to us to uncover its hidden wonders?//Or should we just wait patiently until nature decides to spill the beans?

Text.SourceString: You know, here’s an idea. It might not be a bad thing if I started gardening.//<portrait=normal>After all, I eat a lot of veggies.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, here’s an idea. It might not be a bad thing if I started gardening.//<portrait=normal>After all, I eat a lot of veggies.

Text.SourceString: Maybe… Maybe after the town fixes the community garden, I’ll try my hand at growing something.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe… Maybe after the town fixes the community garden, I’ll try my hand at growing something.

Text.SourceString: Pro tip, <PlayerName>$player</>. Always keep a trusty weapon in your bag, just in case you come across any pesky critters on your journey. You never know!
Text.LocalizedString: Pro tip, <PlayerName>$player</>. Always keep a trusty weapon in your bag, just in case you come across any pesky critters on your journey. You never know!

Text.SourceString: I spent practically the whole day yesterday on a quest for fresh vegetables, but, I still came up empty-handed.
Text.LocalizedString: I spent practically the whole day yesterday on a quest for fresh vegetables, but, I still came up empty-handed.

Text.SourceString: Maybe the lake is a better spot for foraging… Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe the lake is a better spot for foraging… Hmm…

Text.SourceString: I should start leaving my boots by the door.//I track so much mud into the boat, it's a bit of a hassle.
Text.LocalizedString: I should start leaving my boots by the door.//I track so much mud into the boat, it's a bit of a hassle.

Text.SourceString: Ah, I don’t know. Doesn’t sound very convenient.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I don’t know. Doesn’t sound very convenient.

Text.SourceString: I get why some people like to work alone…//<portrait=concerned>It’s nice to have an extra hand, but coordinating can be a pain.
Text.LocalizedString: I get why some people like to work alone…//<portrait=concerned>It’s nice to have an extra hand, but coordinating can be a pain.

Text.SourceString: I’d rather work alone too…//On my own schedule and by my own rules.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d rather work alone too…//On my own schedule and by my own rules.

Text.SourceString: I’m thinking of putting a big, fun bell on the bow of my boat.//<portrait=happy>Like a doorbell for a house.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m thinking of putting a big, fun bell on the bow of my boat.//<portrait=happy>Like a doorbell for a house.

Text.SourceString: That way, no one will ever sneak up on me unawares!//Could be fun, I think…
Text.LocalizedString: That way, no one will ever sneak up on me unawares!//Could be fun, I think…

Text.SourceString: Cooked plenty of food yesterday.//I don’t think I’ll need to make any more until tomorrow.//But I am craving some grilled fish.
Text.LocalizedString: Cooked plenty of food yesterday.//I don’t think I’ll need to make any more until tomorrow.//But I am craving some grilled fish.

Text.SourceString: Maybe… Maybe I can grill just one fish for today. That way I’ll still have to eat up my other food tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe… Maybe I can grill just one fish for today. That way I’ll still have to eat up my other food tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: This island is packed with mysteries, <PlayerName>$Player</>! I've been saying it for ages.//Glad to see someone else thinks so.
Text.LocalizedString: This island is packed with mysteries, <PlayerName>$Player</>! I've been saying it for ages.//Glad to see someone else thinks so.

Text.SourceString: Oh, and listen to this: Exhibit A—this very morning, I discovered a fresh loaf of bread outside my boat.//I wonder who left it there.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, and listen to this: Exhibit A—this very morning, I discovered a fresh loaf of bread outside my boat.//I wonder who left it there.

Text.SourceString: You know what I feel? We're all players in this grand game of life, destined for endless adventures... Yeah...
Text.LocalizedString: You know what I feel? We're all players in this grand game of life, destined for endless adventures... Yeah...

Text.SourceString: Wow! That would be the dream!
Text.LocalizedString: Wow! That would be the dream!

Text.SourceString: I've had my fair share of camping and roasted chestnuts.//It’s safe to say I’m a bit sick of them now. Yuck.
Text.LocalizedString: I've had my fair share of camping and roasted chestnuts.//It’s safe to say I’m a bit sick of them now. Yuck.

Text.SourceString: Here's a little secret: If you didn't listen to the town's chit-chat, you'd never guess that <NPCName>Jim</> is a masterful fisherman.//He doesn’t fish much anymore and doesn’t really talk about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Here's a little secret: If you didn't listen to the town's chit-chat, you'd never guess that <NPCName>Jim</> is a masterful fisherman.//He doesn’t fish much anymore and doesn’t really talk about it.

Text.SourceString: I see myself in <NPCName>Jim</> a lot.//Makes me wonder if I'll ever find true satisfaction and stop seeking new adventures.
Text.LocalizedString: I see myself in <NPCName>Jim</> a lot.//Makes me wonder if I'll ever find true satisfaction and stop seeking new adventures.

Text.SourceString: I used to have a bad allergy to cats.//<portrait=normal>But thankfully, I outgrew it.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to have a bad allergy to cats.//<portrait=normal>But thankfully, I outgrew it.

Text.SourceString: I can play with cats now, but I still sneeze here and there… It’s not bad at all, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I can play with cats now, but I still sneeze here and there… It’s not bad at all, though.

Text.SourceString: Visitors, you ask? No. People don’t visit me…which is cool because I like my space.
Text.LocalizedString: Visitors, you ask? No. People don’t visit me…which is cool because I like my space.

Text.SourceString: Don’t worry about it! I’m sure it’s because I’m away a lot. I rarely spend much time on the boat.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t worry about it! I’m sure it’s because I’m away a lot. I rarely spend much time on the boat.

Text.SourceString: This morning, I found a fresh loaf of bread outside my boat.//I wonder who left it there.
Text.LocalizedString: This morning, I found a fresh loaf of bread outside my boat.//I wonder who left it there.

Text.SourceString: A raccoon, you say? Not convinced. A raccoon would’ve eaten it, I’d think.
Text.LocalizedString: A raccoon, you say? Not convinced. A raccoon would’ve eaten it, I’d think.

Text.SourceString: You know about the treasure chests on this island, right? There are plenty of them in the sea or buried in the cavern.//If you break them open, there may be valuable things in them.
Text.LocalizedString: You know about the treasure chests on this island, right? There are plenty of them in the sea or buried in the cavern.//If you break them open, there may be valuable things in them.

Text.SourceString: A little tip from one treasure hunter to another: Keep your eyes peeled for those chests and give 'em a good whack.
Text.LocalizedString: A little tip from one treasure hunter to another: Keep your eyes peeled for those chests and give 'em a good whack.

Text.SourceString: Those cats… Er…<NPCName>Bread</> and <NPCName>Butter</>? Did I get the names right?//They’re pretty smart.
Text.LocalizedString: Those cats… Er…<NPCName>Bread</> and <NPCName>Butter</>? Did I get the names right?//They’re pretty smart.

Text.SourceString: Yeah! <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>, right… <NPCName>Erika’s</>, right? Yeah. Them.//I see them walking around town at night sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah! <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>, right… <NPCName>Erika’s</>, right? Yeah. Them.//I see them walking around town at night sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I once got into trouble with a client because he wanted his money back. The problem was the government took the treasure I found, and my client sued me for unfinished work.
Text.LocalizedString: I once got into trouble with a client because he wanted his money back. The problem was the government took the treasure I found, and my client sued me for unfinished work.

Text.SourceString: It was a mess. My hands were tied, and I couldn’t do anything about it. Good thing it’s all behind me.
Text.LocalizedString: It was a mess. My hands were tied, and I couldn’t do anything about it. Good thing it’s all behind me.

Text.SourceString: Now that Spring is here, I’m ready to search for treasure again.
Text.LocalizedString: Now that Spring is here, I’m ready to search for treasure again.

Text.SourceString: If you ask me, Spring and Fall are the prime seasons for seeking hidden treasures.//It's not too scorching hot, and the daylight hours are just right.
Text.LocalizedString: If you ask me, Spring and Fall are the prime seasons for seeking hidden treasures.//It's not too scorching hot, and the daylight hours are just right.

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait for the Cherry Blossom Festival. There’s going to be a lot of good food.//And people. Not a bad thing, actually.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait for the Cherry Blossom Festival. There’s going to be a lot of good food.//And people. Not a bad thing, actually.

Text.SourceString: I’m impatient for Spring to get here.//Maybe, just maybe, I have too many leads to chase... But hey, that's part of the thrilling journey.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m impatient for Spring to get here.//Maybe, just maybe, I have too many leads to chase... But hey, that's part of the thrilling journey.

Text.SourceString: Are you ready for the start of a new year, <PlayerName>$player</>? I know I’m raring to go.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you ready for the start of a new year, <PlayerName>$player</>? I know I’m raring to go.

Text.SourceString: The mud can be annoying in Spring, but it’s still better than the bone-chilling Winter for treasure hunting.
Text.LocalizedString: The mud can be annoying in Spring, but it’s still better than the bone-chilling Winter for treasure hunting.

Text.SourceString: What are you bringing for the hot pot, <PlayerName>$player</>? I think I’ll bring whatever fish I manage to catch… Or cookies.
Text.LocalizedString: What are you bringing for the hot pot, <PlayerName>$player</>? I think I’ll bring whatever fish I manage to catch… Or cookies.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice that the sun is up longer, but… Never mind.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice that the sun is up longer, but… Never mind.

Text.SourceString: You never realize how important daylight is until you find yourself scrounging around the woods in the dark, looking for valuables, and end up bringing home a bunch of useless things.//Trash, pretty much… Yeah.
Text.LocalizedString: You never realize how important daylight is until you find yourself scrounging around the woods in the dark, looking for valuables, and end up bringing home a bunch of useless things.//Trash, pretty much… Yeah.

Text.SourceString: I spend a lot of time at the beach in Summer.//Anyway, why wouldn’t I?
Text.LocalizedString: I spend a lot of time at the beach in Summer.//Anyway, why wouldn’t I?

Text.SourceString: I get it, the Beach Cleanup Festival is important, but do they really have to make it an all-day affair?//<portrait=normal>Just a thought, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: I get it, the Beach Cleanup Festival is important, but do they really have to make it an all-day affair?//<portrait=normal>Just a thought, you know?

Text.SourceString: It’s pretty much Fall, and… Wait, no it isn’t.//<portrait=thinking>It’s only the second week of Summer… I thought it was the 20th already.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s pretty much Fall, and… Wait, no it isn’t.//<portrait=thinking>It’s only the second week of Summer… I thought it was the 20th already.

Text.SourceString: The forest is my ultimate go-to hangout spot… Not that I don’t like the sea.//<portrait=happy>But there's something magical about the forest, especially this time of year. Food is abundant, <PlayerName>$Player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: The forest is my ultimate go-to hangout spot… Not that I don’t like the sea.//<portrait=happy>But there's something magical about the forest, especially this time of year. Food is abundant, <PlayerName>$Player</>!

Text.SourceString: When hunger strikes, just wander and forage, then gather 'round a crackling fire.
Text.LocalizedString: When hunger strikes, just wander and forage, then gather 'round a crackling fire.

Text.SourceString: Lately, I've been reeling in quite a haul of groupers.//<portrait=normal>They may not win any beauty contests, that's for sure. But once you grill 'em up, all fish taste pretty much the same.
Text.LocalizedString: Lately, I've been reeling in quite a haul of groupers.//<portrait=normal>They may not win any beauty contests, that's for sure. But once you grill 'em up, all fish taste pretty much the same.

Text.SourceString: I’m not saying you can only eat grilled fish in Fall. Grilled fish is top-tier food that can be enjoyed any time of day, any time of year.//<portrait=happy>But it’s so much better when the weather’s a bit frisky. Like in Fall.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not saying you can only eat grilled fish in Fall. Grilled fish is top-tier food that can be enjoyed any time of day, any time of year.//<portrait=happy>But it’s so much better when the weather’s a bit frisky. Like in Fall.

Text.SourceString: Do you ever find random crabs on your farm?//<portrait=thinking>The rice field <Italic>right</> behind your farm is full of them… This time of year, anyway.//<portrait=normal>Pretty much all I caught the last time I fished there.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you ever find random crabs on your farm?//<portrait=thinking>The rice field <Italic>right</> behind your farm is full of them… This time of year, anyway.//<portrait=normal>Pretty much all I caught the last time I fished there.

Text.SourceString: What am I grilling tonight?//<portrait=thinking>Hmm... I'm leaning towards monkfish. I happen to have some in the fridge, freshly caught from the dock yesterday.
Text.LocalizedString: What am I grilling tonight?//<portrait=thinking>Hmm... I'm leaning towards monkfish. I happen to have some in the fridge, freshly caught from the dock yesterday.

Text.SourceString: There are a lot of delicious things to forage this time of year.//It's a true blessing, really. No need for me to go shopping most days. Nature provides.
Text.LocalizedString: There are a lot of delicious things to forage this time of year.//It's a true blessing, really. No need for me to go shopping most days. Nature provides.

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to <NPCName>Betty’s</> mooncakes. It’s a shame she doesn’t make them more often.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to <NPCName>Betty’s</> mooncakes. It’s a shame she doesn’t make them more often.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been having grilled fish almost every meal for the past two weeks. I think I may have a problem.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been having grilled fish almost every meal for the past two weeks. I think I may have a problem.

Text.SourceString: Daylight is getting shorter and shorter. Looks like I’ll have to stop my exploration pretty soon.
Text.LocalizedString: Daylight is getting shorter and shorter. Looks like I’ll have to stop my exploration pretty soon.

Text.SourceString: You seem pretty much as active in Winter as you are in Summer.//<portrait=happy>Not that I’m keeping tabs… We just seem to travel a lot of the same paths… Well, this year, anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: You seem pretty much as active in Winter as you are in Summer.//<portrait=happy>Not that I’m keeping tabs… We just seem to travel a lot of the same paths… Well, this year, anyway.

Text.SourceString: Since I can’t spend a lot of time out there, I usually read up on the treasures I’m looking for.//The history, clues to their locations, things like that.
Text.LocalizedString: Since I can’t spend a lot of time out there, I usually read up on the treasures I’m looking for.//The history, clues to their locations, things like that.

Text.SourceString: Have you tried tilling the soil on your farm? You might find some stuff…//<portrait=thinking>Oh, but it’s pretty much ice right now, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you tried tilling the soil on your farm? You might find some stuff…//<portrait=thinking>Oh, but it’s pretty much ice right now, huh?

Text.SourceString: Fished a little the other day and caught a green sawfish.//<portrait=normal>Have you tried catching them? You should, since they only come out in wintertime. I caught it right outside your farm… You know where that giant tree is? It was in the body of water across from the hot-air balloon area.//I’d try in the evening. I think they hide during the day.
Text.LocalizedString: Fished a little the other day and caught a green sawfish.//<portrait=normal>Have you tried catching them? You should, since they only come out in wintertime. I caught it right outside your farm… You know where that giant tree is? It was in the body of water across from the hot-air balloon area.//I’d try in the evening. I think they hide during the day.

Text.SourceString: A client once wanted me to search for a chalice in the dead of Winter.//<portrait=annoyed>I said no way, unless he was willing to pay me ten times my usual rate.//<portrait=happy>He gladly waited until Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: A client once wanted me to search for a chalice in the dead of Winter.//<portrait=annoyed>I said no way, unless he was willing to pay me ten times my usual rate.//<portrait=happy>He gladly waited until Spring.

Text.SourceString: It’s not just the cold that makes treasure hunting a pain in Winter. Soil is much harder to dig too… Pretty much concrete at this point.//Better to just wait until the ice melts.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s not just the cold that makes treasure hunting a pain in Winter. Soil is much harder to dig too… Pretty much concrete at this point.//Better to just wait until the ice melts.

Text.SourceString: The boat isn’t really the best place to live in Winter. There’s a lot of wind, and it’s really hard to keep the heat going.
Text.LocalizedString: The boat isn’t really the best place to live in Winter. There’s a lot of wind, and it’s really hard to keep the heat going.

Text.SourceString: Have you ever fished near the mayor’s house in Winter?//I heard from the young fisher you can catch silver arowana there.//<portrait=thinking>Long black hair? Yeah, that’s the one.//<portrait=happy>Oh, the one with bright-red boots, not the one with glasses. She’s not a fisher, I don’t think.//<portrait=thinking>But I don’t really know… Never see her around much.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever fished near the mayor’s house in Winter?//I heard from the young fisher you can catch silver arowana there.//<portrait=thinking>Long black hair? Yeah, that’s the one.//<portrait=happy>Oh, the one with bright-red boots, not the one with glasses. She’s not a fisher, I don’t think.//<portrait=thinking>But I don’t really know… Never see her around much.

Text.SourceString: It’s going to be one hot Summer, isn’t it?//I can already tell.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s going to be one hot Summer, isn’t it?//I can already tell.

Text.SourceString: I went on an adventure to discover a buried temple one time and filled my bag with weapons and no food.//<portrait=normal>I thought there’d be food for me wherever I went. Being not picky and all.
Text.LocalizedString: I went on an adventure to discover a buried temple one time and filled my bag with weapons and no food.//<portrait=normal>I thought there’d be food for me wherever I went. Being not picky and all.

Text.SourceString: I could <Italic>not</> have been more wrong. There was hardly any food, and I ran out of energy in the middle of a battle.//<portrait=annoyed>I passed out and was found by a local blacksmith.
Text.LocalizedString: I could <Italic>not</> have been more wrong. There was hardly any food, and I ran out of energy in the middle of a battle.//<portrait=annoyed>I passed out and was found by a local blacksmith.

Text.SourceString: Don’t make the same mistake I did, <PlayerName>$player</>…//Pack some food.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t make the same mistake I did, <PlayerName>$player</>…//Pack some food.

Text.SourceString: You’re not the only new person here.//Have you met <NPCName>Surya</>?
Text.LocalizedString: You’re not the only new person here.//Have you met <NPCName>Surya</>?

Text.SourceString: He moved here just before you did.//<portrait=normal>Heard it was for coral reef restoration. He’s some sort of doctor, I believe. Not the medical kind.
Text.LocalizedString: He moved here just before you did.//<portrait=normal>Heard it was for coral reef restoration. He’s some sort of doctor, I believe. Not the medical kind.

Text.SourceString: Have you met <NPCName>Scott</>?//I see him at the cavern every now and then.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you met <NPCName>Scott</>?//I see him at the cavern every now and then.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been collecting clues about this island’s secrets.//Though I put my mission off for the Winter and decided to enjoy the weather instead. I can’t wait to get going again.//<portrait=happy>Now that it’s Spring, I’ll continue my adventure.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been collecting clues about this island’s secrets.//Though I put my mission off for the Winter and decided to enjoy the weather instead. I can’t wait to get going again.//<portrait=happy>Now that it’s Spring, I’ll continue my adventure.

Text.SourceString: The question is, will I find anything new today?
Text.LocalizedString: The question is, will I find anything new today?

Text.SourceString: You look all sweaty. Long day at the farm?
Text.LocalizedString: You look all sweaty. Long day at the farm?

Text.SourceString: I learn something new every day on this island if I look closely enough.
Text.LocalizedString: I learn something new every day on this island if I look closely enough.

Text.SourceString: The heat is exhausting.
Text.LocalizedString: The heat is exhausting.

Text.SourceString: But there are plenty of wild vegetables growing.//That’s a good thing for someone like me, who relies on nature a lot for food.
Text.LocalizedString: But there are plenty of wild vegetables growing.//That’s a good thing for someone like me, who relies on nature a lot for food.

Text.SourceString: I heard you worked in a big city before becoming a farmer.
Text.LocalizedString: I heard you worked in a big city before becoming a farmer.

Text.SourceString: Oh, that’s right! I heard about that.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, that’s right! I heard about that.

Text.SourceString: That makes sense. I can tell from your outfit. It’s very…um…artistic.
Text.LocalizedString: That makes sense. I can tell from your outfit. It’s very…um…artistic.

Text.SourceString: Ah, I see.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I see.

Special.SourceString: Yes. I ran a small company from my apartment.
Special.LocalizedString: Yes. I ran a small company from my apartment.

Text.SourceString: Of course studying counts! Good luck with that. I believe we never really stop learning.
Text.LocalizedString: Of course studying counts! Good luck with that. I believe we never really stop learning.

Special.SourceString: Does studying count? I was a student. In a way, still am.
Special.LocalizedString: Does studying count? I was a student. In a way, still am.

Text.SourceString: Ah! What’s that like? I feel like we’re all in a big simulation game sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah! What’s that like? I feel like we’re all in a big simulation game sometimes.

Special.SourceString: I made games. It’s really fun, but it’s not as easy as I thought it was going to be.
Special.LocalizedString: I made games. It’s really fun, but it’s not as easy as I thought it was going to be.

Text.SourceString: All righty, then. Good day to you.

Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know too much about farming, but they say Spring is the perfect time to plant those colorful flowers.

Text.SourceString: I don't really need 'em on my boat. My gem collection brings enough colors to my world.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't really need 'em on my boat. My gem collection brings enough colors to my world.

Text.SourceString: Coral Island is always beautiful this time of year.//<portrait=normal>It’s beautiful year-round, but it really blooms in the Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: Coral Island is always beautiful this time of year.//<portrait=normal>It’s beautiful year-round, but it really blooms in the Spring.

Text.SourceString: The Summer haze makes adventuring much more enjoyable. Everything feels heavy, still, and mysterious.
Text.LocalizedString: The Summer haze makes adventuring much more enjoyable. Everything feels heavy, still, and mysterious.

Text.SourceString: Do you think we’ll get any storms soon, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I’d rather know ahead of time if they’re coming.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think we’ll get any storms soon, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I’d rather know ahead of time if they’re coming.

Text.SourceString: If a storm’s coming, I have to prep my boat… It’s a long process.
Text.LocalizedString: If a storm’s coming, I have to prep my boat… It’s a long process.

Text.SourceString: Having a Summer birthday isn’t too bad. It means I get extra hours of daylight to celebrate.
Text.LocalizedString: Having a Summer birthday isn’t too bad. It means I get extra hours of daylight to celebrate.

Text.SourceString: Not that I do much celebrating, though.//That’s not really my style.
Text.LocalizedString: Not that I do much celebrating, though.//That’s not really my style.

Text.SourceString: Feel that slight chill in the air? Winter's creeping closer, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//Time to bundle up and brace ourselves for some chilly days ahead.
Text.LocalizedString: Feel that slight chill in the air? Winter's creeping closer, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//Time to bundle up and brace ourselves for some chilly days ahead.

Text.SourceString: I feel closest to nature in Fall. The beautiful colors, piles of leaves on the ground… It’s something to be thankful for.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel closest to nature in Fall. The beautiful colors, piles of leaves on the ground… It’s something to be thankful for.

Text.SourceString: Grilled fish are delicious this time of year. I catch them from my boat and cook them myself.
Text.LocalizedString: Grilled fish are delicious this time of year. I catch them from my boat and cook them myself.

Text.SourceString: It’s a good, warm meal for cold nights.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a good, warm meal for cold nights.

Text.SourceString: All this snow on the ground means buried treasure is harder to find. It’s no fun to dig through wet snow, either.
Text.LocalizedString: All this snow on the ground means buried treasure is harder to find. It’s no fun to dig through wet snow, either.

Text.SourceString: The ocean may rage with storms in Summer, but it can be just as bad in Winter.//And it’s a lot colder.
Text.LocalizedString: The ocean may rage with storms in Summer, but it can be just as bad in Winter.//And it’s a lot colder.

Text.SourceString: As much as I love my boat, I feel a little trapped during Winter.//I don’t want to stay inside, but I don’t want to go out into the cold air, either.
Text.LocalizedString: As much as I love my boat, I feel a little trapped during Winter.//I don’t want to stay inside, but I don’t want to go out into the cold air, either.

Text.SourceString: Some people escape to Winter houses in warmer climates when it gets too cold outside.//I suppose I could move my boat somewhere warmer in Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: Some people escape to Winter houses in warmer climates when it gets too cold outside.//I suppose I could move my boat somewhere warmer in Winter.

Text.SourceString: I like Coral Island too much to do that, though. I’ll just make sure to keep the heat on all the time.
Text.LocalizedString: I like Coral Island too much to do that, though. I’ll just make sure to keep the heat on all the time.

Text.SourceString: I'm not afraid to get down and dirty. Grime, dust, you name it—I've embraced it all.//But you know what I despise? Getting wet. Ugh, it's the worst!
Text.LocalizedString: I'm not afraid to get down and dirty. Grime, dust, you name it—I've embraced it all.//But you know what I despise? Getting wet. Ugh, it's the worst!

Text.SourceString: I wish I could stick around and talk, but I want to stay as dry as possible.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could stick around and talk, but I want to stay as dry as possible.

Text.SourceString: It’s easy to slip when it’s dark and rainy like this, especially when you’re walking on a wet deck.//Be careful.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s easy to slip when it’s dark and rainy like this, especially when you’re walking on a wet deck.//Be careful.

Text.SourceString: Look at it pour out there. Do you think it’ll clear up soon?
Text.LocalizedString: Look at it pour out there. Do you think it’ll clear up soon?

Text.SourceString: Even when I’m safely inside for the night, I can still feel the rain hitting the deck and the roll of the waves outside.//At least it’s not too windy.
Text.LocalizedString: Even when I’m safely inside for the night, I can still feel the rain hitting the deck and the roll of the waves outside.//At least it’s not too windy.

Text.SourceString: Going somewhere?
Text.LocalizedString: Going somewhere?

Text.SourceString: Thankfully, I bought some supplies for the boat the other day.//You know…flour, eggs, cookies…the usual.//<portrait=thinking>It’d be annoying to be outdoors when it storms like this.
Text.LocalizedString: Thankfully, I bought some supplies for the boat the other day.//You know…flour, eggs, cookies…the usual.//<portrait=thinking>It’d be annoying to be outdoors when it storms like this.

Text.SourceString: I just can’t stay focused on this book.
Text.LocalizedString: I just can’t stay focused on this book.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I should just go to bed. I’m not going to get anything accomplished while the weather is this bad.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I should just go to bed. I’m not going to get anything accomplished while the weather is this bad.

Text.SourceString: Snow makes me just as soggy as rain does. Like a stale chip…//…Left too long between the couch cushions.
Text.LocalizedString: Snow makes me just as soggy as rain does. Like a stale chip…//…Left too long between the couch cushions.

Text.SourceString: I was supposed to go spelunking today, but I had to postpone it because of this snow. I guess I’ll just stay close to home for now.
Text.LocalizedString: I was supposed to go spelunking today, but I had to postpone it because of this snow. I guess I’ll just stay close to home for now.

Text.SourceString: I like watching the snow melt as it hits the ocean. It just piles up if it lands on my boat.
Text.LocalizedString: I like watching the snow melt as it hits the ocean. It just piles up if it lands on my boat.

Text.SourceString: Looks like I’ll have shoveling to do tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Looks like I’ll have shoveling to do tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Hey, <PlayerName>$player</>. Did you come to see me or my boat?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, <PlayerName>$player</>. Did you come to see me or my boat?

Text.SourceString: Living on a boat isn’t much different from living on land. I still have to make sure I have enough food, supplies, and medicine.
Text.LocalizedString: Living on a boat isn’t much different from living on land. I still have to make sure I have enough food, supplies, and medicine.

Text.SourceString: The only real difference is I can take my home everywhere I go.//<portrait=normal>I like that.
Text.LocalizedString: The only real difference is I can take my home everywhere I go.//<portrait=normal>I like that.

Text.SourceString: The fish aren’t biting today.//I might have to eat something else for dinner.
Text.LocalizedString: The fish aren’t biting today.//I might have to eat something else for dinner.

Text.SourceString: When it comes to preparing fish, there are a gazillion ways to do it. But let me tell you, nothing beats the sizzling goodness of grilling.//<portrait=normal>It really brings out the flavor.
Text.LocalizedString: When it comes to preparing fish, there are a gazillion ways to do it. But let me tell you, nothing beats the sizzling goodness of grilling.//<portrait=normal>It really brings out the flavor.

Text.SourceString: I wasn’t big on fishing before I moved here, but sometimes there’s not much else to do on the water besides catch a few trout.
Text.LocalizedString: I wasn’t big on fishing before I moved here, but sometimes there’s not much else to do on the water besides catch a few trout.

Text.SourceString: I like to spend my days off here. It feels good to stretch my legs and sit under the sky.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to spend my days off here. It feels good to stretch my legs and sit under the sky.

Text.SourceString: As much as I love the water, sometimes it’s nice to see some green too.
Text.LocalizedString: As much as I love the water, sometimes it’s nice to see some green too.

Text.SourceString: I'd lend you my metal detector, but, uh, I'm actually using it at the moment.
Text.LocalizedString: I'd lend you my metal detector, but, uh, I'm actually using it at the moment.

Text.SourceString: It's a blast sifting through the sand and discovering all sorts of hidden treasures.//It's like a special treat, especially when I find something cute that I can give to the kiddos.
Text.LocalizedString: It's a blast sifting through the sand and discovering all sorts of hidden treasures.//It's like a special treat, especially when I find something cute that I can give to the kiddos.

Text.SourceString: I brought some food along, but I have a feeling it might be a bit on the stale side.//<portrait=happy>Oh well, fingers crossed it's still somewhat edible.
Text.LocalizedString: I brought some food along, but I have a feeling it might be a bit on the stale side.//<portrait=happy>Oh well, fingers crossed it's still somewhat edible.

Text.SourceString: Volleyball isn't really my thing.//That ball is massive, and I gotta admit, it kind of scares me. I mean, imagine getting whacked by that thing.
Text.LocalizedString: Volleyball isn't really my thing.//That ball is massive, and I gotta admit, it kind of scares me. I mean, imagine getting whacked by that thing.

Text.SourceString: Ah, the wind is nice here.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, the wind is nice here.

Text.SourceString: You gotta be careful when eating your lunch here...there's sand everywhere.
Text.LocalizedString: You gotta be careful when eating your lunch here...there's sand everywhere.

Text.SourceString: I'd rather bring my own coconuts. The beach shack has them, but gosh, they're pricey!//I mean, sure, they offer them cold, but I'd rather save a few bucks.
Text.LocalizedString: I'd rather bring my own coconuts. The beach shack has them, but gosh, they're pricey!//I mean, sure, they offer them cold, but I'd rather save a few bucks.

Text.SourceString: The lake is a nice change of pace from the beach and the ocean.
Text.LocalizedString: The lake is a nice change of pace from the beach and the ocean.

Text.SourceString: The sand here is certainly less gritty.
Text.LocalizedString: The sand here is certainly less gritty.

Text.SourceString: I should talk to <NPCName>Walter</> about the possibility of a new job. His family must have another lost heirloom I can search for.
Text.LocalizedString: I should talk to <NPCName>Walter</> about the possibility of a new job. His family must have another lost heirloom I can search for.

Text.SourceString: There are plenty of gems on this island. I found several rare ones digging around the cavern the other day.
Text.LocalizedString: There are plenty of gems on this island. I found several rare ones digging around the cavern the other day.

Text.SourceString: You and I… We aren’t too different.//Neither of us is from here, and you don’t seem to mind a little adventure.
Text.LocalizedString: You and I… We aren’t too different.//Neither of us is from here, and you don’t seem to mind a little adventure.

Text.SourceString: It’s cool. Never thought I’d make a friend here on Coral Island.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s cool. Never thought I’d make a friend here on Coral Island.

Text.SourceString: Consider taking any artifact you find to the museum first and having <NPCName>Scott</> inspect it. Chances are, the island might not have it on file.
Text.LocalizedString: Consider taking any artifact you find to the museum first and having <NPCName>Scott</> inspect it. Chances are, the island might not have it on file.

Text.SourceString: But hey, you don’t have to.//<portrait=happy>You can also sell that stuff. I do it all the time.
Text.LocalizedString: But hey, you don’t have to.//<portrait=happy>You can also sell that stuff. I do it all the time.

Text.SourceString: Pretty sure I saw a couple of birds flying around and carrying twigs this morning.
Text.LocalizedString: Pretty sure I saw a couple of birds flying around and carrying twigs this morning.

Text.SourceString: I think they were building a new nest.//<portrait=happy>I don’t usually get all warm and fuzzy, but that was really cute.
Text.LocalizedString: I think they were building a new nest.//<portrait=happy>I don’t usually get all warm and fuzzy, but that was really cute.

Text.SourceString: You know what? I like the way your mind works… It’s never a dull conversation with you.
Text.LocalizedString: You know what? I like the way your mind works… It’s never a dull conversation with you.

Text.SourceString: I never knew how delicious jam was until I went on an adventure for an entire season on a secluded island.//It was in the middle of nowhere. At the time, I ate mainly raw wild vegetables, and all I’d brought was four jars of my mom’s jam.
Text.LocalizedString: I never knew how delicious jam was until I went on an adventure for an entire season on a secluded island.//It was in the middle of nowhere. At the time, I ate mainly raw wild vegetables, and all I’d brought was four jars of my mom’s jam.

Text.SourceString: Favorite jam? Hmm… Hang on now. Jam isn’t my favorite food.//<portrait=normal>I just think it’s delicious to indulge in when you have nothing better to eat. That said, I don’t have any favorite jam. I think for me, any jam will do.
Text.LocalizedString: Favorite jam? Hmm… Hang on now. Jam isn’t my favorite food.//<portrait=normal>I just think it’s delicious to indulge in when you have nothing better to eat. That said, I don’t have any favorite jam. I think for me, any jam will do.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… What should I do this weekend?
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… What should I do this weekend?

Text.SourceString: Parents can be too much to handle sometimes.//<portrait=concerned>Mine are always nagging me about coming home.
Text.LocalizedString: Parents can be too much to handle sometimes.//<portrait=concerned>Mine are always nagging me about coming home.

Text.SourceString: They’re trying to be supportive, though. They never give me a hard time about my…journeys.//<portrait=concerned>But a lot of times the fear shows anyway, and the inevitable nagging follows. Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: They’re trying to be supportive, though. They never give me a hard time about my…journeys.//<portrait=concerned>But a lot of times the fear shows anyway, and the inevitable nagging follows. Hmm…

Text.SourceString: I love what you did with the lot, by the way...right, your grandparent's farm. It’s not abandoned like it was before.//<portrait=happy>You have an eye for these things.
Text.LocalizedString: I love what you did with the lot, by the way...right, your grandparent's farm. It’s not abandoned like it was before.//<portrait=happy>You have an eye for these things.

Text.SourceString: I thought settling down in one place would be boring until… Well, until I met you, actually.
Text.LocalizedString: I thought settling down in one place would be boring until… Well, until I met you, actually.

Text.SourceString: This island is so much more fun when we explore together.
Text.LocalizedString: This island is so much more fun when we explore together.

Text.SourceString: It was hard for me to tell my family that what made me happy was leaving home and exposing myself to daily danger…//<portrait=annoyed>But that was the truth, and they brought me up to be a <Italic>truth-teller</>…//<portrait=blushing>It’s this thing my dad used to say.
Text.LocalizedString: It was hard for me to tell my family that what made me happy was leaving home and exposing myself to daily danger…//<portrait=annoyed>But that was the truth, and they brought me up to be a <Italic>truth-teller</>…//<portrait=blushing>It’s this thing my dad used to say.

Text.SourceString: Mom was way too emotional about it. But I’m glad she…er…at least tried to understand.//I can only imagine the worry I put my parents through.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom was way too emotional about it. But I’m glad she…er…at least tried to understand.//I can only imagine the worry I put my parents through.

Text.SourceString: I never used to keep secrets from my mom… Not until I lived on my own.//<portrait=annoyed>I hate this new dynamic, but…I feel it’s best to keep her out of the loop sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: I never used to keep secrets from my mom… Not until I lived on my own.//<portrait=annoyed>I hate this new dynamic, but…I feel it’s best to keep her out of the loop sometimes.

Text.SourceString: With my injuries, the places I have to sleep when I’m on the job, and the food that…er…//Anyway, Mom wouldn’t be able to handle it. I’d hate to break her heart over and over again.
Text.LocalizedString: With my injuries, the places I have to sleep when I’m on the job, and the food that…er…//Anyway, Mom wouldn’t be able to handle it. I’d hate to break her heart over and over again.

Text.SourceString: I notice there’s always fresh flowers at the temple, and yet I’ve never found out who puts them there. Your doing?
Text.LocalizedString: I notice there’s always fresh flowers at the temple, and yet I’ve never found out who puts them there. Your doing?

Text.SourceString: I don’t care about a lot of people, but I do care deeply about my family, my friends… And you.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t care about a lot of people, but I do care deeply about my family, my friends… And you.

Text.SourceString: I know you go to the cavern a lot. So if you need backup, please come to me.//I hate the thought of you being down there alone. Just…let me look out for you.
Text.LocalizedString: I know you go to the cavern a lot. So if you need backup, please come to me.//I hate the thought of you being down there alone. Just…let me look out for you.

Text.SourceString: I should send my parents some pumpkins.//They like Coral Island’s pumpkins… Sweetest ones they ever tasted, they said.
Text.LocalizedString: I should send my parents some pumpkins.//They like Coral Island’s pumpkins… Sweetest ones they ever tasted, they said.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I can throw in a birthday card for my dad too. His birthday is the first of Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I can throw in a birthday card for my dad too. His birthday is the first of Winter.

Text.SourceString: I don’t even want to think about it, but gosh!//<portrait=surprised02>I woke up thinking about moving to another island… Nightmares. That did it to me.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t even want to think about it, but gosh!//<portrait=surprised02>I woke up thinking about moving to another island… Nightmares. That did it to me.

Text.SourceString: It isn’t all bad, I think…moving to another island.//<portrait=blushing>It’s just… I’ve already made a lot of friends here.//<portrait=normal>It would be a waste to leave now, don’t you think?
Text.LocalizedString: It isn’t all bad, I think…moving to another island.//<portrait=blushing>It’s just… I’ve already made a lot of friends here.//<portrait=normal>It would be a waste to leave now, don’t you think?

Text.SourceString: I really like your hair that way. Suits you.
Text.LocalizedString: I really like your hair that way. Suits you.

Text.SourceString: You look very…errr…cute.
Text.LocalizedString: You look very…errr…cute.

Text.SourceString: I like to keep my distance, not be too, er…chummy with the townies.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to keep my distance, not be too, er…chummy with the townies.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know. I guess some of them seem…nosy. Always asking a few too many questions.//That scares me for whatever reason.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know. I guess some of them seem…nosy. Always asking a few too many questions.//That scares me for whatever reason.

Text.SourceString: If you want, you’re welcome to stay at my place sometime.//It’ll give you an idea of what boat living is like. But you better do it during Fall or Spring. That’s when the current isn’t as wild, not right now.
Text.LocalizedString: If you want, you’re welcome to stay at my place sometime.//It’ll give you an idea of what boat living is like. But you better do it during Fall or Spring. That’s when the current isn’t as wild, not right now.

Text.SourceString: I warn you, though, it’s not for everybody.//<portrait=happy>But I have a feeling you’re gonna like it.
Text.LocalizedString: I warn you, though, it’s not for everybody.//<portrait=happy>But I have a feeling you’re gonna like it.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>, I was just thinking about how lucky I am that I get to go on adventures with you.
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>, I was just thinking about how lucky I am that I get to go on adventures with you.

Text.SourceString: I always thought I would go adventuring alone, that I didn’t need anyone to go with me.//I’m glad you’re here, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I always thought I would go adventuring alone, that I didn’t need anyone to go with me.//I’m glad you’re here, though.

Text.SourceString: Would you ever want to live on a boat?//I wouldn’t want you to abandon your farm or anything, but…I wouldn’t mind sharing with you.
Text.LocalizedString: Would you ever want to live on a boat?//I wouldn’t want you to abandon your farm or anything, but…I wouldn’t mind sharing with you.

Text.SourceString: You’re sparkling today, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re sparkling today, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: Errr… You’re the most incredible gem I’ve ever found.//Gosh! That was cheesy…//I hope you like cheesy.
Text.LocalizedString: Errr… You’re the most incredible gem I’ve ever found.//Gosh! That was cheesy…//I hope you like cheesy.

Text.SourceString: This might sound strange, but I’m getting used to seeing you in here. You’re part of my home now.//<portrait=surprised>Ha ha! <Italic>No!</> Not like a piece of furniture.//<portrait=normal>Like a family member.
Text.LocalizedString: This might sound strange, but I’m getting used to seeing you in here. You’re part of my home now.//<portrait=surprised>Ha ha! <Italic>No!</> Not like a piece of furniture.//<portrait=normal>Like a family member.

Text.SourceString: Could you see the two of us living in a space like this?//<portrait=normal>Finding hidden treasures and traveling the world? I think it would be the journey of a lifetime.
Text.LocalizedString: Could you see the two of us living in a space like this?//<portrait=normal>Finding hidden treasures and traveling the world? I think it would be the journey of a lifetime.

Text.SourceString: Have you ever sat on this pier at sunset? The view is beautiful.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever sat on this pier at sunset? The view is beautiful.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice to not think about anything for a while and just enjoy the colors.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice to not think about anything for a while and just enjoy the colors.

Text.SourceString: Could you hand me some more bait, <PlayerName>$player</>? I need to refresh my hook.
Text.LocalizedString: Could you hand me some more bait, <PlayerName>$player</>? I need to refresh my hook.

Text.SourceString: Ooh, your hand is clammy! Is everything okay?//<portrait=concerned>You can sit here with me for a bit if you need to.
Text.LocalizedString: Ooh, your hand is clammy! Is everything okay?//<portrait=concerned>You can sit here with me for a bit if you need to.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I have dreams about huge fish that pull on my line so hard I fall into the water.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I have dreams about huge fish that pull on my line so hard I fall into the water.

Text.SourceString: You have them too?!//What are the odds! That’s an amazing coincidence.
Text.LocalizedString: You have them too?!//What are the odds! That’s an amazing coincidence.

Text.SourceString: I know I’m not always there for you…but know that I’ll try to be there when you need me, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: I know I’m not always there for you…but know that I’ll try to be there when you need me, okay?

Text.SourceString: I really like you, but I like me too…and being alone is part of who I am.//<portrait=normal>I hope it doesn’t offend you when I ask for some time alone.
Text.LocalizedString: I really like you, but I like me too…and being alone is part of who I am.//<portrait=normal>I hope it doesn’t offend you when I ask for some time alone.

Text.SourceString: In weather like this, I’m grateful I didn’t skimp on the cost of this boat.//The cheaper model didn’t have as good a heating and cooling system.
Text.LocalizedString: In weather like this, I’m grateful I didn’t skimp on the cost of this boat.//The cheaper model didn’t have as good a heating and cooling system.

Text.SourceString: But it did leave a big dent in my bank account.
Text.LocalizedString: But it did leave a big dent in my bank account.

Text.SourceString: Farming sure has a lot of...routine. Not really my style, <PlayerName>$player, but I can see why you enjoy it.
Text.LocalizedString: Farming sure has a lot of...routine. Not really my style, <PlayerName>$player, but I can see why you enjoy it.

Text.SourceString: Ever just look at the stars and wonder what’s beyond there? Maybe one day, I'll pack my bags and set off for the unknown...just not today.
Text.LocalizedString: Ever just look at the stars and wonder what’s beyond there? Maybe one day, I'll pack my bags and set off for the unknown...just not today.

Text.SourceString: I wonder what's at the bottom of the ocean. You think it's all just rocks and fish, or is there a sunken city waiting to be discovered?
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what's at the bottom of the ocean. You think it's all just rocks and fish, or is there a sunken city waiting to be discovered?

Text.SourceString: Had a close encounter with a shark the other day. Scary, but thrilling at the same time. Makes you feel alive.
Text.LocalizedString: Had a close encounter with a shark the other day. Scary, but thrilling at the same time. Makes you feel alive.
